<subSubSection id="EBAF651CC2376F27FF308D6BFBE85A11" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A30A3697C2376F27FF308D6BFBE85A11" blockId="6.[166,1225,1598,1848]" lastBlockId="7.[174,1232,1483,1701]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
D i a g n o s i s. Head yellow, antenna and frontal vitta dark yellow; ventral half of median occipital sclerite and occiput lateral of it widely black or brown, widely yellow emarginated. Flagellomere 1 pointed apically. Scutum black, with 4 gray microtrichose vittae. Wing pattern with four brown bands, without intercalary band; apical band separated from costa by hyaline area in cells r 
<subScript id="3F3134D2C2376F26FE558D84FE4A5ACB" attach="left" box="[446,473,1745,1759]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">2+3</subScript>
and r 
<subScript id="3F3134D2C2376F26FDF18D84FDA75ACB" attach="left" box="[538,564,1745,1759]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">4+5</subScript>
(
<figureCitation id="3B8E2A12C2376F26FDAB8DEBFDE95ACC" box="[576,634,1726,1752]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,1755,1777]" captionTargetBox="[261,1137,1047,1737]" captionTargetId="figure-482@5.[253,1161,1027,1746]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Palearctic species of Rhagoletis species similar to R. merzi, wings: a — R. zernyi; b — R. flavigenualis; c — R. merzi, sp. n.; d — R. bagheera; e — R. batava. Bands are marked as follows: A — apical, D — discal, SA — subapical, SB — subbasal. Red arrow shows connection of D and SA; cyan arrow shows cr — crescentic hyaline area. Scale: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6456142" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6456142/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, d). Femora dark brown to black. Abdomen black, tergites with yellow posterior margins. This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="64B54D14C2376F26FC768D8AFB9F5AEC" authorityName="Hering" authorityYear="1958" box="[925,1036,1758,1784]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Rhagoletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batava">
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C2376F26FC768D8AFC3C5AEC" box="[925,943,1759,1784]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C2376F26FC568D8BFB9F5AEC" box="[957,1036,1758,1784]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">batava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="64B54D14C2376F26FBA38D8AFB3A5AEC" authorityName="Korneyev &amp; Smith &amp; Hulbert &amp; Frey &amp; Korneyev" authorityYear="2022" box="[1096,1193,1758,1784]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Rhagoletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="merzi">
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C2376F26FBA38D8AFBC95AEC" box="[1096,1114,1759,1784]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C2376F26FB8C8D8AFB3A5AEC" box="[1127,1193,1759,1784]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">merzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in general appearance and femora coloration, but is conspicuously smaller (body length = 
<quantity id="644D9B72C2376F26FF4D8C4BFEA65B2C" box="[166,309,1822,1848]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="2.8" valueMax="2.9" valueMin="2.7">2.7–2.9 mm</quantity>
and wing length = 
<quantity id="644D9B72C2376F26FDCC8C4BFD505B2C" box="[551,707,1822,1848]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.28" metricValueMax="2.36" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="2.28" valueMax="2.36" valueMin="2.2">2.2–2.36 mm</quantity>
for 
<taxonomicName id="64B54D14C2376F26FD128C4AFC175B2C" authorityName="Richter &amp; Kandybina" authorityYear="1997" box="[761,900,1822,1848]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Rhagoletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bagheera">
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C2376F26FD128C4AFC985B2C" box="[761,779,1823,1848]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C2376F26FCF08C4BFC175B2C" box="[795,900,1822,1848]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">bagheera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
,&gt; 
<quantity id="644D9B72C2376F26FC458C4BFC655B2C" box="[942,1014,1822,1848]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName id="64B54D14C2376F26FBCA8C4AFB015B2C" authorityName="Hering" authorityYear="1958" box="[1057,1170,1822,1848]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Rhagoletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batava">
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C2376F26FBCA8C4AFBA05B2C" box="[1057,1075,1823,1848]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C2376F26FBA88C4BFB015B2C" box="[1091,1170,1822,1848]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">batava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="64B54D14C2366F27FF458E99FE8659F1" authorityName="Korneyev &amp; Smith &amp; Hulbert &amp; Frey &amp; Korneyev" authorityYear="2022" box="[174,277,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Rhagoletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="merzi">
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C2366F27FF458E99FF5359F1" box="[174,192,1484,1509]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C2366F27FF388E99FE8659F1" box="[211,277,1484,1509]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">merzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and has different host plants: 
<taxonomicName id="64B54D14C2366F27FD498E9EFC8259F1" box="[674,785,1483,1509]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhamnaceae" genus="Rhamnus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C2366F27FD498E9EFC8259F1" box="[674,785,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Rhamnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="64B54D14C2366F27FCCD8E9EFC5259F2" box="[806,961,1483,1510]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhamnaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rhamnaceae</taxonomicName>
) for 
<taxonomicName id="64B54D14C2366F27FBE88E99FB0259F1" authorityName="Richter &amp; Kandybina" authorityYear="1997" box="[1027,1169,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Rhagoletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bagheera">
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C2366F27FBE88E99FB8659F1" box="[1027,1045,1484,1509]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C2366F27FBC38E9EFB0259F1" box="[1064,1169,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">bagheera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="64B54D14C2366F27FF458EBEFEBE5A11" box="[174,301,1515,1541]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Elaeagnaceae" genus="Hippophae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C2366F27FF458EBEFEBE5A11" box="[174,301,1515,1541]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Hippophae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="64B54D14C2366F27FED78EBEFE4F5A12" box="[316,476,1515,1542]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Elaeagnaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Elaeagnaceae</taxonomicName>
) for 
<taxonomicName id="64B54D14C2366F27FDF88EB9FD125A11" authorityName="Hering" authorityYear="1958" box="[531,641,1515,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Rhagoletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batava">
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C2366F27FDF88EB9FDB65A11" box="[531,549,1516,1541]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C2366F27FDD98EBEFD125A11" box="[562,641,1515,1541]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">batava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="64B54D14C2366F27FD508EB9FCB95A11" authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[699,810,1516,1541]" class="Pinopsida" family="Cupressaceae" genus="Juniperus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C2366F27FD508EB9FCB95A11" box="[699,810,1516,1541]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Juniperus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="64B54D14C2366F27FCD28EBEFC4F5A12" box="[825,988,1515,1542]" class="Pinopsida" family="Cupressaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Cupressaceae</taxonomicName>
) for 
<taxonomicName id="64B54D14C2366F27FBFF8EB9FBE75A11" authorityName="Korneyev &amp; Smith &amp; Hulbert &amp; Frey &amp; Korneyev" authorityYear="2022" box="[1044,1140,1515,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Rhagoletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="merzi">
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C2366F27FBFF8EB9FBB55A11" box="[1044,1062,1516,1541]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C2366F27FBD98EB9FBE75A11" box="[1074,1140,1516,1541]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">merzi</emphasis>
